Yes, it was by Hans.

>>It also totally changes the feel of the setting (I\'ve tried it). I\'d
>>suggest avoiding it... but it is wonderfully written. It also is not
>>supportive of existing canon.
>
>Really? Tell me more (either here or by e-mail if you don\'t think it would
>interest others). What did you try? What went wrong? And why do you think it
>isn\'t supportive of existing canon as a whole? I mean, I know it contradicts
>some canon, but that is because (IMO, of course) canon contradicts itself
>(Specifically, if you count Imperial nobles from the top down, you get
>10,000 or perhaps 100,000 peers, while if you count from the bottom up, you
>get tens or hundred of millions).
>
It confirmed what I felt (and told you via extensive discussion off list oh
those years ago)... It was too complex for my player group; It meant that
the PC\'s who were elevated for service were not, in fact, imperial nobles,
and thus didn\'t count (or so was the players\' contention); it added nothing
positive to the feel of nobility, but did detract from the experience. It
also made the players (One of whom was soc 15) very reluctant to even stop
in to the local imperial baron on a Social call, let alone seek him out as
a potential patron, source of info, or even social contact.

If one has imperial nobility so far separated, the ability of PC\'s to FEEL
connected to the imperium is reduced.

I use the following base-lines... The local ruler is also an Imperial
Baron, count or viscount. All Local nobility are knights or barons on the
imperial scale. A Major World with subordinate governments (such as a local
multi-system polity which joined as a polity, rather than individual
worlds) would have their leader an Imperial Marquis. IMTU, All barons and
higher have voice in the moot, regaurdless of type; only those in service
to the imperium have a vote, and most send proxies to trusted associates
on/near capital.

In GURPS terms, make local ranks cheaper (ala courtesy ranks). If Imperial
Social rank is 5 pts/level, A Major world should be 3 pts a level, and a
minor one 2. Reduce each by 1 point if honor title.

