>
>*something all Traveller players should read, if only for great looking
>ships. Jesse, if you ever get the chance consider doing one of the Jovian
>Chronicles ships, I suspect it would be damn dificult, they aren\'t
>smooth-hulled like Traveller ships, more like Bab5 EarthForce ships.

JC is a wonderfully written game. It has a decent set of rules; a simple
and consistant mechanic. The mechanics are a hybrid of tactical wargame and
roleplaying skill systems. The vehicle design system is more a rating
system, which also tells you how big it MUST be (as a range), based upon
the basic tech level of the system. Not to mention it is compatable with
Heavy Gear and Tribe 8. But, the system overall, while well written and
simple, looks to lend it self more to dice-rolling than role-playing. (I
have not yet run any of the DP9 stuff except as solo-combat bits). Best
non-FTL RPG setting I\'ve read. Much better than Terradyne. Setting with
details as rich and mineable for ideas as S1889.

I do agree, however, that it should eb looked at, especially the books on
ships. Great feel for TL9, extended duration, in-system ships. Note: Trav
TL 9 is pregravitic, and late TL 9 is jump capable.

