    'month' => '12',
    'body' => '>As long as we\'re telling weather habituation stories,
>let\'s not forget my college classmates who came from
>Ghana and Nigeria and were suddenly confronted with
>their first Pennsylvania autumn -- "how can you stand
>this horrible cold?" they asked, as the temperature
>hovered around 60F.  They were wearing down jackets in
>September.  I don\'t know how they survived December
>and January. 

Reminds me of a time back in my college days, where one
of the local public library branches had a library
assistant from Australia visit on a six-month exchange,
from mid-June to mid-December. She came to talk to our
class one time, Library Science being my field of study.
Later that fall we had class sweatshirts made for ourselves,
and had a few extras made. One, we gave to the visiting
Australian. This was in early November. She remarked that
this was a very appropriate gift, what with how cold it
was getting -- temperatures down around -5 C (about 25 F).
The branch head librarian, who was with us when we gave
her the shirt, remarked "This is nothing -- wait until it
gets down to minus 40!" The Australian library assistant
almost choked on her coffee on that one...

(It didn\'t get down to -40 until about six weeks after she
returned to Australia...)


