    'date' => 'Mon, 13 Dec 1999 21:29:27',
    'body' => 'At 10:43 AM 12/14/1999 +1300, you wrote:

>Ob Trav: How many Travellers, other than the PCs, go to low Law Level 
>worlds just to use/purchase weapons they normally aren\'t allowed?

Well, consider the cost.. Assume that the world you want to purchase
weapons on is J-1 away.  That\'s Cr. 16,000 at least to have a fairly good
chance of living through the journey.  After that, there\'s the problem of
residency.  I can\'t just cross the border into Oregon or Nevada and go
shopping, the dealer will want to see my ID.  It\'s a violation of federal
to knowing sell an illegal firearm, and since whatever toy I\'ve come all
the way to another state to buy is probably banned in California (which is
the safest state in the country, just take a night-time stroll through East
LA!) they can\'t sell it to me.

In Traveller, I think customs would be very curious about people making
short trips to lower law level worlds.  Baggage searches would be common.
- -- 

