    'body' => 'At 11:53 AM 12/13/1999 -0500, you wrote:

>Im just hoping to be retired before the tents, boots, and gas mask get
>lighter. I dont want to carry ladders and winches on my back so we can
>always be ready in an urban environment.

Suddenly remembered one of the funniest moments of my military life.

We were doing MOUT exercises.  The Company CO had promised a day off on the
next Friday for the squad with the fastest time in getting into a second
story window.  This normally entails throwing a grappling hook through the
window and climbing up.  As we went along, the average time was hovering
around six or seven minutes.  The First Sergeant called for one of 2nd
Platoon\'s squads, who had vanished into the tree line about 20 meters away.

They appeared at a dead run, carrying a 12 foot long tree trunk that they
had trimmed the branches off of, leaving short stumps.  Two men took cover
positions while the rest of the squad swarmed up this improvised ladder
into the room.  Total time, about 45 seconds.

Needless to say, they got the day off.
- -- 

