his BD Mercs (Don\'t ask... Please... Suffice it to say Xen and Hamford DO
know the Guy in question.)... The result, a TL15 2mm (2x20mm DU Slug) HVSB
Carbine and Pistol system, done under 3G3... a DU 2x20mm slug, propelled by
near max safe caseless load (TL15 powder, calc\'ed by 3G3 methods as
3G3TL17), stepping out at Mach-8 at 1atm.... Pen was ridiculous, Damage
(MT) was 3 if soft armor or no armor and 8 otherwise. As a ballance factor,
I had the pistol throw 2m of flame, plus a sonic boom from hell. The
Carbine was only marginally better, having still almost as much wase
energy, but more accuracy. After reversion to MT stats, the differences
were concealability and atten differing. Sig was (by GM Fiat) VHigh...
hardened ear protection required (MT Dmg 1 if not, per shot). The Carbine
was equipped with a Full Auto selectable reciever; the pistol was semi
only. Prices were set unrealistically high due to VERY low demand, but it
could effectively negate TL15 BD... if you could hit it. Also, the
extremely compact ammo meant high volumes of ammo in the basic load.

