they got caught by Bighampton or his aide, and need to convince McHale
to spring them. Or maybe Mchale got caught and the players have to
convince the admiral that he\'s innocent.

McHale and crew would liven up any system or subsector. And just about
*any* of the shows can be turned into a quickie subplot or encounter. 

Heck after a few encounters, just noticing that McHale or one of his
patrol boats is in the same port ought to raise the paranoia level
considerably. Sure, whatever he\'s up (if he\'s even up to anything)
*probably* won\'t affect that players. But leaving port quickly will
seem like a *really* good idea. :-)

