    'body' => 'In mail you write:

> How are starship payments figured? In the book it says (from memory...) its
> 20% down payment plus 1/240th every month for 480 months giving a total
> return of 240% to the bank.
>
> What RL model is this using? Is there a handy formula for the effect of
> differing years or if extra is paid?

Check out formulas for calculating loans at differing interest rates.
Plug in the principal (cost of ship minus the down payment), the term
(40 years), the payment interval (monthly) and solve for the interest
rate. I expect that you\'ll be surprised how *low* it is. The more
payments you make (actually the longer the period you make them over)
the more that interest eats up. Your early payments can be 90% or more
interests with only the remainder actually reducing the principal. 

