    'body' => 'Kyle Schuant wrote:

> Finland, what a glorious nations, where the most
> repressive gun laws are noise pollution laws!

	There are two sides in each coin.

	We have to apply for a license for each gun separately, and it 	
	always includes a background check (it takes one week). The 
	recent changes in Finnish gun laws made it more clear what is 
	required for gun license application.

	Basically, if a person can provide a "legally acceptable 
	reason" why he needs a certain type of weapon, the license will 
	be granted (you can\'t apply a machine pistol for "duck 
	hunting").

	If the applied weapon is very unusual, the local police will 
	refuse the application ("wash their hands"), and the application 
	must be re-send to the district headquarters. As far as I know, 
	the district headquarters has not refused any reasonable 
	applications.

	Because of EU legal homogenization, we now need a separate 
	license for purchasing "dangerous" ammunition. Various types of 
	expanding and fragmenting bullets are considered dangerous (this 
	comes from German gun laws), but the ERVA license can be 
	obtained very easily (it took me ~3 minutes of talking).

	The net effect of tightened gun laws was that we need one more 
	license, and can buy just about any weapon if we can provide 
	reason for buying it.

	(Err... sorry about this rambling. Legal/political/social
	issues are largely beyond my understanding. Back to Traveller)


	In Traveller I have assumed that starship crew and passengers 
	need either local or "general" gun license (depending on local 
	Law Level) if they want to carry personal weapons when they 
	leave the ship.

	In Imperium the imperial nobles might be considered as being 
	"above" the local laws, but in Solomani Confederation I have 
	assumed that there is a kind "Confederate gun license" which 
	allows the holder to carry personal small-arms within the 
	confederation (SolSec personnel would have this kind of 
	license which supersedes the local restrictions).

- -- 
      Antti Lahtinen                lahtinen@ee.tut.fi
      Researcher, MSc (Eng)         http://www.ee.tut.fi/~lahtinen
