The US Marines did, in fact, use cutlases in their early days. The marine
NCO dres side-arm, accroding to the LPM, is still the cutlass. Officers use
a mamaluke hitled sword. Early US marines carried cutlasses in addition to
Muskets (NS1 and NS2 NROTC/NJROTC texts). Also remember, US Marines ARE
(Technically) "Naval Personell" (the USMC is part of the Department of the
Navy).

