I think Tommy makes an important point about violence.
Well educated and materially comfortable people are
less likely to be violent than uneducated and poor
people.  I won\'t speculate as to causes, but I think
that the correlation is real.  (It\'s also pretty well
recognized that the only factor related to declines in
the birth rate across cultures is increased
education.)  
Traveller doesn\'t have UPP codes for general education
level and standard of living, although these are
obviously very important factors in trying to
understand what a place will be like.  How might we
arrive at numbers for these factors, using the
information that we have? 

Conceivably all of the other UPP codes and trade
classifications relate to them.  

A slightly more subtle factor to add to an expanded
UPP might be wealth disparity.  The average per capita
income might be Cr10,000, but 1% of the population
might be getting MCr1 while 95% are getting only
Cr1,000.  This is a very different planet than one
with the same average per capita income but 85% of the
population is getting it.  How could we come up with a
code for this?

- --Glenn


