The exact effect of the D&D3\'s pricing on the market is pretty much 
speculation at this point.  There is the distinct possibility that the only 
thing that happens is that WotC cuts their profit margin and sales don\'t 
spike as they hope.

 From my POV, I don\'t think that D&D3 will be a bad thing for the 
industry.  I think it will shake things up a bit, but anything that gets 
people into the hobby is good for the entire hobby.  Hence, products like 
GURPS Lite and "entry level" games (like the $10 D&D and Alternity boxed 
sets) are great tools for bringing people into the industry.
