    'date' => 'Fri, 17 Dec 1999 09:52:44 +1000',
    'body' => '> From: Glenn Goffin 
> The really nasty conflicts involve the Ine Givar, who
> will stop at nothing to achieve independence from the
> Imperium -- even if it means that Jewell, Regina,
> Vilis, and Lanth subsectors become a Zhodani
> protectorate.  The Ine Givar\'s primary demands are
> total freedom to practice psionics and a restructuring
> of the economy to ownership by the state.  

IMTU, the Ine Givar are heavily factionalised, so there are groups that
disagree with all their demands.  

That said, other common demands are respect for the rights of non-humans
(especially Vargr, and Dandies), and various permutations of democracy and
independence.  Pro-Sword Worlds factions tend to water down the
pansophontist demands (being a bunch of Solomani-chauvinist backsliding
scum), while some of the pro-Zhodani/pro-psionics oriented groups still
favour Zhodani-style psionic oligarchy, despite being in a distinct
minority in the IG.

The pansophontism gives rise to some interesting conflicts, where the Ine
Givar end up supporting Vargr communities threatened by human supremacist
groups, like Rule of Terra and Superioriti.  Of course the Vargr themselves
are often quite capable of defending themselves, and on occasion will
remind human mobs what the word "Corsair" means.

Going OT:  the above is actually influenced by some posts I got on another
list, on the topic of gun control!  Apparently, the civil rights movement
in the US, one of the classic "nonviolent" movements, was defended by a
very large proportion of its members possessing guns.  This resulting in
the white hood brigade suffering some very embarrassing setbacks....  

