    'index' => 'eh334',
    'body' => 'Personally I run a pretty canonical TU, but I don\'t worry about minor
details.  For instance, I have vector direction randomized on jump exit. 
There are several canonical sources which specifically mention ships
heading in certain directions so that they\'ll emerge going in certain
directions, so that\'s not "official".  But I think it fits better with the
overall OTU, in which near-c rocks are not commonly used.

Oh, but I am a heretic when it comes to rules.  I\'ve never really run any
system "out of the box", I always tweak with house rules. I think almost
everybody does this with Traveller, because the system is simple enough to
modify easily.  And of course now I\'m using FUDGE to run my games.  <FUDGE
PLUG (Man, that sounds obcene!)>God that system is so freeing!  I ran a
Traveller adventure a few weeks ago and an impromtu "Heros in Hell" game
after that, using the same rules with virtually no prep.  It\'s very smooth
(and its free...).</FUDGE PLUG>


Charles C.
