	Culture is Very High. However, about the "barrelcrash"...

	Roughly similar events has also happened in real life. Currently 
	most warheads (at least those used in man-portable weapons) have 
	a "camo-net safety" which prevents the detonator from working 
	before the warhead has flown several meters from the launcher.

	Before camo-net safety was introduced, mortar crews were 
	sometimes killed when their grenades hit overhanging foliage or 
	camo nets.

