    'topic' => ' Wealth Distribution UPP value',
    'index' => 'eh423',
    'month' => '12',
    'body' => 'One way to do this would be to generalize the old "20% of the people have
80% of the wealth" statistic.  Each level of the Wealth Dist UPP value
would be a 5% jump.  0 would mean that a very few people (less than 2.5%) 
owned virtually everything (more than 97.5%).  10 would mean that 50% of
the people controlled 50% of the wealth, a very egalitarian society in
socio-ecomonic terms.  Present day earth is about a 4, IIRC. The letter
designations could be reserved for special things such as "no personal
ownership" or "continuous flux in wealth distribution (gift economy?)". 

The basic idea is that you line everybody up in order of wealth and put
down a marker at each increase of 10% in wealth, then determine where the
point of equilibrium is (ie. where percent of people equals 100 minus
percent of wealth).  If I\'m thiking straight (and it\'s early, so no
guarantee) this should give you a basic measure of the non-linearity of 
your wealth distribution curve...

Charles C.
