is a federal matter, while in the USA it\'s a state matter (except for
federal crimes). So we have one Criminal Code for the entire country.

>The socialized medicine thing would have to go, however.

We don\'t have "socialized medicine" -- we have a publicly-funded universal
health care insurance plan. Think of it as a "single-payer" system like
I keep reading about that some people down your way propose.

(In a true "socialized medicine" system, doctors are employees of the 
state and are paid a flat salary; private practice is virtually unknown.
I have relatives in Europe in countries that have socialized medicine --
when they need a doctor, the only thing they can do is go to the local
clinic and wait for the next availble doctor, whoever it might be.)

