As an occasional photographer I often travel with an old medium format twin
lens reflex camera or two.  If you\'ve never seen one they are a rather large
rectangular box type camera with two lenses on the front.   You focus by
looking down into a screen on the top.  If they are loaded I always have
them hand checked.   Airport security invariably checks such cameras by
looking through the view screen at the top ignoring the fact that they have
second large film chamber at the bottom... remember it\'s a "twin lens"
camera not a single lens reflex.  Such people look but they don\'t see.  If I
have the time, an empty camera and there is no line I occasionally educate
them by removing the lens board and showing them how to check one properly.
I figure the life I save may be my own.

On the flip side on one occasion I had an officious old biddy open every one
of the 35 mm plastic film cans I had in the bag, my guess is that she was
looking for dope.  On a second occasion I had to stop security from opening
a factory sealed box of unexposed 8 by 10 inch sheet film for one of my
large format cameras.   I told him he was welcome to break the seal and open
it if he wanted to but if he did so he bought it and I wanted the twenty
five bucks up front.

Dan
