>
>- --
>Josh

We know that Solomani and Vilani can interbreed, assuming you accept DGP
materials; The vilani purity table was a dead giveaway. We know that there
are individuals of Mixed solomani ancestry (AM Solomani, GDW). We know that
you can tell zhodani purebreed and solomani purebreed apart by counting
teeth. Since we never saw an AM Vilani from GDW, their details are a little
fuzzier.

Darrians are a human minor race, too. Even if they do show some 40-50
thousand years adaptations (or more). We know that they can interbreed, but
we are not shown (in AM 8, nor elsewhere I have seen) 2nd generation
hybrids.

We are not shown in GDW materials any other specific human minors of note
in detail; The hlasani are not humaniti. We are told there are others, but
not shown details of any of them.

We are shown a human minor race whose differences are the matter of having
been adapted to by a symbiote, the result is a "shaggy", whose fur is the
xenofungi symbiote; it protects the human host from the local atmospheric
taint, and draws sustinence through the human. It also suppresses the human
intellect.

If one accepts the DGP materials, then we see several more human minors.
The Jonkereen are the only ones I know to have been fully detailed,
however.

Unfortunately, we have seen references to several distinct groups of human
minors races, but not had them detailed by DGP.

Peter Newman\'s work in my campaign (and after) on one human minor show the
difficulties; he\'s still trying to add to them. Their canon reference is a
one-liner. (I have temporarily blanked on the race\'s name.) Likewise, the
Geonee, in canon, have many references, but no details.

Several third party supplements have referenced human minors; Judges guild
had at least 3 human minors with only slightly more detail than the canon
references to the Geonee... but at least JG specified their homeworlds....

William F. Hostman  |  "Smith & Wesson: THe original Point and Click
