    'subj' => 'Gun Control - KNOCK IT OFF!',
    'from' => 'Jeff Zeitlin jzeitlin@cyburban.com',
    'body' => 'I have never had any problem discussing gun control or other
government stupidities.  I am very opinionated on the matter of
the Constitution of the United States, and I can argue my views
cogently and intelligently, without resorting to ad hominems.  I
do so regularly, both in my workplace and in conversations with
my father and my friends.

I had a perfect opportunity to do so here a few days ago.
However, this is the Traveller Mailing List, and gun control in
the United States of America is not the topic of the list
(although gun control on Ruie, Muan Gwi, Sylea, or Dlan might
very well be).  I therefore chose to send my response to the
poster privately.  We have since had an enlightening discussion
via private mail, in greater depth than would be convenient or
comfortable here.  I urge the members of this list who are
interested in pursuing this non-Traveller discussion to follow
suit.

Naturally, if a discussion on gun control or other government
stupidities in a Traveller environment were to start here, I
would, with great enthusiasm, contribute appropriate amounts of
gasoline, napalm, and other similarly appropriate substances,
with the intent of encouraging such discussion.  But only in a
Traveller context, please.

I trust I have made my point clearly and inoffensively.
- --
