    'from' => 'stoo.dollar@worldnet.att.net',
    'body' => 'On 18 Dec 99, at 17:06, Jim & Peta Lawrie wrote:

>     I have always loved the scenario "Marooned (Alone)", it was travelling
> at its best. Stuck on a planet with a nebulous time limit (and an S-series)
> hanging over your head. I was looking at it again last night and I noticed
> the survival weapon, eg Rifle -2.

This scenario brings back memories.

One of the scenarios we designed and ran during T4\'s day for 
GenCon \'97 was an updated version of Marooned.  I came up with a 
bit of a new spin on the scenario that made it a lot more fun.  

During the opening minutes of the scenario, after the ship has been 
fatally damaged, but before the characters make good their 
escape, we had several random rolls on a set of "Scrounged 
Equipment Tables".  These would be things that maybe people 
hurriedly grabbed out of their cabins, looted from other cabins or 
elsewhere on the ship, etc.  As a natural extension of this, we put 
a whole lot less survival gear on the lifeboat itself...

Because of the random nature of this, players would often wind up 
with unusual equipment (a shotgun, but no ammo...lots of water, 
no food, etc.).  Incidentally, we recorded the roll results secretly 
with the individual players, so none of the PCs knew what the 
others had...and since this was a convention setting, not too many 
of the players knew each other either...it was a great way to break 
the ice as the PCs spent the first few minutes trying to figure out 
what they had as a group...

Stu
