    'body' => '>Lack of political will had nothing to do with it, nor was it an american
>chance to grab british territory.  The brits started with the invasion and
>then realized that Napoleon was going to be a tougher enemy than anticipated.
> They could not fight two major wars and so they chose to take on the closer
>enemy.  The yanks saw the brit drawel and said fine, we\'ll follow up to
>prevent future invasions.

Are you implying Britain invaded the US first during the war of 1812?
Do they even *teach* Americans history these days?

A quick outline would be
(0) Britain is conscripting british (and occasional American) soliders out
of British ships. America doesn\'t like this. Also, Britain is blocking
American trade with France (more legitimately). And there are all these
nice Canadian colonies sitting there apparently undefended...
Negotiations on the shipping stuff actual reached a compromise, but
too late, so
(1) Therefore, the US starts the war, invading Canada, expecting an
easy victory
(2) To the US\' surprise, they get their tails kicked
(3) The US wins some surpring victories in one-on-one engagements
at sea, although
(4) Britain decisively blockades US ports
(5) Once the penninsular war is over, Britain takes a bunch of veteran
troops and invades and burns Washington, but doesn\'t attempt to hold
it (which they probably couldn\'t have done)
(6) Instead, Britain invades in the south, heading for New Orleans
(7) Peace is negotiated
(8) Since the commanders haven\'t heard about the peace, British and
US soliders fight at New Orleans; the US wins the battle.

"Draw" is a good description. America got its maratime rights respected
and a lot of prestige from some otherwise-unimportant naval actions;
Britain got to burn washington and didn\'t lose Canada, but did lose the last
major land battle of the war.

It is actually somewhat Traveller relevant in that it was a war dominated by
communication delays - if news of negotiations had reached Washington
in time war might not have been declared, and of course the last
battle was fought after the war was technically over.

Bruce
